This is a port of Linux kernel for the RISC-V architecture.
Development is currently based on the 3.5 mainline branch.

Obtain RISC-V architecture-dependent subtree and overlay sources from upstream:

	$ git clone https://github.com/ucb-bar/riscv-linux.git linux-3.5-rc5
	$ wget -q -O - http://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v3.0/testing/linux-3.5-rc5.tar.bz2 | tar -xjk

Apply patch to scripts/mod/modpost.c to avoid segfaulting on little-endian
64-bit kernel builds:
http://www.linux-mips.org/archives/linux-mips/2006-04/msg00130.html

	$ cd linux-3.5-rc5
	$ patch -p1 < modpost.patch

Generate default kernel configuration:

	$ gmake ARCH=riscv defconfig

Edit configuration via an ncurses interface:

	$ gmake ARCH=riscv menuconfig

Build static kernel image:

	$ gmake ARCH=riscv vmlinux

Run the kernel image:

	$ fesvr -nopk vmlinux

